Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Lightly grease an 8 inch square pan. In a large bowl, combine sugar, shortening, spices, salt, soup, and raisins. Stir in boiling water. Cool. Sift the flour, baking powder, and baking soda together. Add to the cooled raisin mixture, and stir until just combined. Pour batter into prepared pan. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes. Serve warm.